{"sha": "e40a6fb1336bb2025b2ef348c7caf4b4f39d90cd", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0NzI0NzEyOmU0MGE2ZmIxMzM2YmIyMDI1YjJlZjM0OGM3Y2FmNGI0ZjM5ZDkwY2Q=", "commit": {"author": {"name": "kennytm", "email": "kennytm@gmail.com", "date": "2018-01-12T18:26:30Z"}, "committer": {"name": "GitHub", "email": "noreply@github.com", "date": "2018-01-12T18:26:30Z"}, "message": "Rollup merge of #47298 - cramertj:path-as-modrs, r=nikomatsakis\n\nTreat #[path] files as mod.rs files\n\nFixes https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/46936, cc @briansmith, @SergioBenitez, @nikomatsakis.\n\nThis (insta-stable) change treats files included via `#[path = \"bla.rs\"] mod foo;` as though they were `mod.rs` files. Namely, it allows them to include `mod` statements and looks for the child modules in sibling directories, rather than in relative `modname/childmodule.rs` files as happens for non-`mod.rs` files.\n\nThis change makes the `non_modrs_mods` feature backwards compatible with the existing usage in https://github.com/briansmith/ring, several versions of which are currently broken in beta. If we decide to merge, this change should be backported to beta.\n\ncc https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/37872\n\nr? @jseyfried", "tree": {"sha": "f3b9db2afc2275dae287b0b0fa27dfe4d093b22b", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/trees/f3b9db2afc2275dae287b0b0fa27dfe4d093b22b"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/git/commits/e40a6fb1336bb2025b2ef348c7caf4b4f39d90cd", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/e40a6fb1336bb2025b2ef348c7caf4b4f39d90cd", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/commit/e40a6fb1336bb2025b2ef348c7caf4b4f39d90cd", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/commits/e40a6fb1336bb2025b2ef348c7caf4b4f39d90cd/comments", "author": {"login": "kennytm", "id": 103023, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjEwMzAyMw==", 